on driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:168:  the per-class gate in the dynamic-access workflow and the terminal\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:174:- [Coverage improvement workflow](improve-library-coverage.md) — generates\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:175:  additional tests to improve dynamic-access coverage on an existing library\n../4649-a9dbf980/stats/io.netty/netty-transport/4.1.115.Final/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 0.363636,\n../4649-a9dbf980/stats/io.netty/netty-transport/4.1.115.Final/stats.json:8:          \"coveredCalls\" : 8,\n../4649-a9dbf980/stats/io.netty/netty-transport/4.1.115.Final/stats.json:12:      \"coverageRatio\" : 0.363636,\n../4649-a9dbf980/stats/io.netty/netty-transport/4.1.115.Final/stats.json:13:      \"coveredCalls\" : 8,\n../4649-a9dbf980/stats/io.netty/netty-transport/4.1.115.Final/stats.json:18:        \"covered\" : 8888,\n../4649-a9dbf980/stats/io.netty/netty-transport/4.1.115.Final/stats.json:24:        \"covered\" : 2417,\n../4649-a9dbf980/stats/io.netty/netty-transport/4.1.115.Final/stats.json:30:        \"covered\" : 664,\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:41:> [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:142:where `<class-key>` is a sanitized form of the dynamic-access class the\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:402:| Dynamic-access workflow | [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md) |\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:9:  - `run(...)`: runs a single generation attempt. It generates the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to `BasicIterativeStrategy` only if no usable guidance exists at the start, otherwise enters the dynamic-access class iteration immediately and counts success only after metadata generation, retest, `generateLibraryStats`, and a commit for the library iteration succeed.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:10:  - `__init__(...)`: keeps the dynamic strategy config minimal by requiring only the class-specific dynamic-access prompt and dynamic-access-specific iteration limits, while providing internal defaults for the start-of-run basic fallback prompts and fallback iteration limits.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:11:  - `_run_dynamic_access_phase(...)`: uncovered-class iteration using coverage deltas from dynamic-access reports; initializes `exhausted_classes = set()` for the phase, emits targeted prompts per uncovered class, includes the current uncovered dynamic-access call-site list in every prompt, retries `./gradlew test` failures inside a bounded per-class mini-loop by sending the failing output back to the agent, clears agent context after each class attempt sequence, treats the phase as successful once any dynamic-access call site becomes covered, enforces per-class prompt-attempt limits, and fails the generation if the dynamic-access report disappears mid-phase.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:14:  - `_format_progress(...)`: renders per-class progress summary (attempt count, newly covered call sites, remaining uncovered call sites) for prompt context.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:17:  - `load_dynamic_access_coverage_report(...)`: parses JSON report payload into typed dataclasses.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:18:  - `compute_class_delta(...)`: compares previous/current report for one class and computes newly covered vs still-uncovered call sites.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:19:  - `format_call_sites(...)`: converts uncovered/newly-covered call-site lists into prompt-ready bullet text.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:53:    Strategy->>Report: `load_dynamic_access_coverage_report(...)`\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:60:        loop For each uncovered class until resolved or exhausted\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:61:            Strategy->>Report: Select next uncovered class and format progress\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:63:                Strategy->>Agent: Render class-targeted prompt with uncovered call sites\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:75:                Report-->>Strategy: Newly covered and still-uncovered call sites\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:79:                else Class still has uncovered call sites\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:80:                    Note over Strategy,Report: Retry the same class with updated uncovered call sites.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:82:                    Note over Strategy,Report: Advance to the next uncovered class.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:7:> **See also:** [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:37:The gate is the per-class success criterion for the dynamic-access workflow\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:52:| Output directory | Caller | Absolute path. The caller picks a path namespaced per (library, class) for the dynamic-access caller, or per coordinate for non-class-scoped callers — same convention as [native-metadata-exploration.md §4](native-metadata-exploration.md#4-output). On `PASSED`, the gate merges all accepted per-cycle trace dirs into this directory (one `mergeNativeTraceMetadata` invocation). |\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:188:| `dynamic_access_iterative` per-class loop ([dynamic-access-wo