ies.md:39:        DAReport[(\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\")]\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:87:    Inc -->|coverage phase| Dyn\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:164:- **Required prompts**: `dynamic-access-iteration`.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:165:- **Required params**: `max-iterations` (per uncovered class),\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:167:- **Loop**: parses `dynamic-access-coverage.json`; iterates over classes with\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:168:  uncovered call sites. For each class it renders the iteration prompt with\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:169:  uncovered call-site lists and the coverage delta, runs the inner test loop,\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:171:  coverage increases (even partially). A class is \"exhausted\" after\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:182:- **Required prompts**: `optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration`.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:185:  uncovered call sites) in a single prompt, then runs the inner test loop. On\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:187:  early when every call site is covered.\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:191:### 3.4 `increase_dynamic_access_coverage` (composite)\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:193:[`increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py`](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py)\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:200:  primary succeeds, runs `dynamic_access_iterative`'s per-class coverage\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:201:  phase to lift coverage further. If the primary fails, returns its result\n../4649-a9dbf980/forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:236:| `increase_dynamic_access_coverage` | `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.4`, `javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_